### Step 4 — Add Users to Their Security Groups

1. In **Active Directory Users and Computers**, find the Security Group in its OU
2. Right-click the group → **Properties** → **Members** tab
3. Click **Add** → type the username → **Check Names** → **OK**
4. Click **Apply** → **OK**

#### Group Membership

| Security Group | Members |
|---|---|
| `GRP-IT-HelpDesk` | ajohnson, bcarter |
| `GRP-HR` | mjones, slee |
| `GRP-Finance` | dkim, rturner |
| `GRP-Management` | jwilson, lscott |

#### Verify Group Members via PowerShell

```powershell
Get-ADGroupMember -Identity "GRP-IT-HelpDesk" | Select Name
Get-ADGroupMember -Identity "GRP-HR" | Select Name
Get-ADGroupMember -Identity "GRP-Finance" | Select Name
Get-ADGroupMember -Identity "GRP-Management" | Select Name
```

