## Part 3 — Testing Share Access from Windows 11

### Step 1 — Access the Shares

1. Log into **Windows 11** with a domain user (e.g. `ajohnson`)
2. Open **File Explorer** and type the server path in the address bar:
```
\\Ceres-DC-01
```
3. You should see all shared folders listed

### Step 2 — Verify Permissions Are Working

| Logged in as | Can Access | Should Get Access Denied |
|---|---|---|
| ajohnson (IT) | IT-HelpDesk | HR, Finance, Management |
| mjones (HR) | HR | IT-HelpDesk, Finance, Management |
| dkim (Finance) | Finance | IT-HelpDesk, HR, Management |
| jwilson (Management) | Management | IT-HelpDesk, HR, Finance |

> 💡 **Note:** Getting **Access Denied** on other department folders is the expected and correct result — it confirms your Security Group permissions are working properly.

