## Part 4 — Mapping a Network Drive

> 💡 **Interview Tip:** Mapping a network drive is one of the most frequently asked IT help desk interview questions. Know this step by step.

1. On **Windows 11**, open **File Explorer**
2. Right-click **This PC** → **Map Network Drive**
3. Choose a **Drive Letter** (e.g. `Z:`)
4. Enter the folder path:
```
\\Ceres-DC-01\IT-HelpDesk
```
5. Check **"Reconnect at sign-in"** so the drive persists after reboot
6. Click **Finish**

The department folder will now appear as a mapped drive under **This PC** in File Explorer.

